premise_source_doc_sentence: Work -- family enrichment or work -- family facilitation refers to a process at the work-life interface whereby experience or participation in one role increases the quality or performance in the other role .
Enrichment of facilitation can occur when involvement in one role leads to benefits , resources , and/or personality enrichment which then may improve performance or involvement in the other role .

Family-work enrichment occurs when involvement within the family results in the creation of a positive mood , feeling of support , or feeling of success which can help that individual to cope better , more efficient , more confidence , or recharged for one 's role at work .

The main psychiatric approaches to treatment for persons diagnosed with gender dysphoria are psychotherapy or to support the individual 's preferred gender through hormone therapy , gender expression and role , or surgery .
In the English literature , there is also a trichotomy between biological sex , psychological gender , and social gender role .
